.TH VENTURI 1 "April 2026" "0.1.0" "Venturi Manual"
.SH NAME
venturi \- DAG-native programming language runtime
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B venturi
[\fICOMMAND\fR] ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B venturi
is a runtime for the Venturi domain-specific language. It executes files and directories as Directed Acyclic Graphs (DAGs). Venturi enforces strict data-flow constraints, making it ideal for robust ETL pipelines, orchestrations, and reactive GUIs.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR run " " \fI<FILE>\fR
Parse and execute a single .vt file.
.TP
.BR run-dag " " \fI<DIR>\fR
Load all .vt files in a directory, build the DAG, and execute.
.TP
.BR chass " " \fI<DIR> \fR--output\fR \fI<FILE> \fR[--mode \fI<MODE>\fR] [--name \fI<NAME>\fR]
Compile a directory of .vt files into a .vcbin binary format.
.TP
.BR vcbin " " \fI<SUBCMD>\fR
Inspect or verify a .vcbin file. Subcommands: \fBinfo\fR, \fBverify\fR.
.TP
.BR pit " " \fI<SUBCMD>\fR
Manage hot-update pits. Subcommands: \fBcreate\fR, \fBupdate\fR, \fBrollback\fR, \fBstatus\fR, \fBlist\fR.
.TP
.BR validate " " \fI<FILE>\fR
Validate a .vt file (parse + check, no execution).
.TP
.BR graph " " \fI<DIR>\fR
Print the DAG topology for a directory of .vt files.
.TP
.BR gui " " [--dir \fI<DIR>\fR] [--backend \fI<egui|iced>\fR]
Launch the VenturiCards GUI from a gui-app DAG directory.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.venturi/pits.json
Configuration and state for Venturi pits (hot-update modules).
